fields.title: Conversational English
fields.label: S
fields.description: Conversational English lesson focuses on helping learners develop fluency and practice verbal communication with native English speakers. This is primarily intended for those learners who need quick assistance with being more encouraged to communicate in English.

fields.title: General English
fields.label: P
fields.description: General English, is exactly what it sounds like– English for general purposes. It aims to give language learners a firm foundation in basic grammar and communication. It focuses on developing the core skills of reading, writing, listening, and oral skills, through a wide range of topics. This course contains 10 lessons in total.

fields.title: English for Specific Purposes
fields.label: S
fields.description: English for specific purposes (ESP) is a subset of English as a second or foreign language. It usually refers to teaching the English language to university students or people already in employment, with reference to the particular vocabulary and skills they need. This is organized as an individual lesson or especially, if needed, as an individually tailored course. The price is fixed.

fields.title: IELTS Preparation
fields.label: P
fields.description: Prepare for your test with a range of free IELTS study materials and resources. The first step in making sure you are ready to take IELTS is to prepare for it so you know what to expect on the test day. Our IELTS learning materials will get you acquainted with the test format and also improve your confidence when writing, speaking, reading, and listening in English. Even if you believe you are a proficient user of English, we still recommend that you prepare thoroughly for your test with our helpful IELTS training resources. This course consists of 10 lessons.

fields.title: Writing Course
fields.label: P
fields.description: Writing course aims at improving various aspects of learners' writing skills. This course contains 5 lessons with a general learning plan followed throughout it/can be also individually tailored if the learner requests that.

fields.title: Business English
fields.label: P
fields.description: Business English course provides language instruction and training in business communication, including business correspondence, negotiations, formal presentations, informal networking, business vocabulary, report and proposal writing, vocabulary for professional purposes, and reading for professional purposes. This course contains 8 lessons in total.

fields.title: Pronunciation Workshop
fields.label: P
fields.description: Designed specifically for non-native English speakers Improve your communication and pronunciation instantly with proven vocal training techniques This course consists of 5 lessons.

fields.title: Grammar Workshop
fields.label: P
fields.description: In this practical workshop, you’ll get a refresher on the rules of punctuation and grammar. You’ll also learn to identify common errors – and see how you can fix them. For example, we’ll look at: What goes into a sentence? What’s a quick way to check that a sentence is grammatically correct? When do you use ‘that’ and ‘which’? What’s the difference between ‘affect’ and ‘effect’? What’s the best practice in writing numbers and dates? This and many other questions can be answered within this grammar workshop. The course consists of 10 lessons.
